The tendency of reformers to appeal to the greatness of the past and, to rely on scripturalauthority encouraged mysticism. These contributed in compartmentalizing Hindus, Muslims, Sikhs andParsis. Thus, the movement helped alienating high caste Hindus from low caste Hindus to some extent.
